## Development Guidelines
### Modern Browser Focus
- Utilize modern JavaScript and Web APIs without polyfills
- Use modern CSS features like Grid, Flexbox, and CSS Variables

### Tooling
- Always use pnpm to install dependencies

### Component Design
- Separate logic and data handling from UI rendering
- Structure directories around features
- Use early returns for better readability
- Use functional components and hooks
- Use Tailwind classes for styling
- Implement proper accessibility features

### Code Style
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Prefix event handlers with "handle" (e.g., handleClick, handleKeyDown)
- Use "class:" instead of ternary operators for class names
- Implement proper error handling